casebody.data:
David BURNET, Commissioner of Internal Revenue, v. NEWBLOCK OIL COMPANY OF TEXAS. NO. 793. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Jan. 21, 1933. C. M. Charest, General Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. Erwin Bruce Hallett, of New York City, for respondent.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Petition for review dismissed on motion of petitioner.
